## Summary Table

| | Multithreading | Multiprocessing |
|---|---|---|
| **Memory** | Shared | Isolated |
| **Parallelism (Python)** | ❌ (GIL) | ✅ True parallel |
| **Best for** | I/O-bound | CPU-bound |
| **Overhead** | Low | Higher (fork cost) |
| **Communication** | Easy (shared vars) | Harder (queues/pipes) |
| **Crash isolation** | ❌ One thread can corrupt all | ✅ Processes are isolated |

---

> **Key mental model:** threads wait together, processes work in parallel. The OS is always the one deciding who gets CPU time — your job is to structure the work so the OS can keep all cores busy.
